244    /**
245    * Creates a pie chart with default settings that compares 2 datasets.
246    * The colour of each section will be determined by the move from the value
247    * for the same key in <code>previousDataset</code>. ie if value1 > value2
248    * then the section will be in green (unless <code>greenForIncrease</code>
249    * is <code>false</code>, in which case it would be <code>red</code>).
250    * Each section can have a shade of red or green as the difference can be
251    * tailored between 0% (black) and percentDiffForMaxScale% (bright
252    * red/green).
253    * <p>
254    * For instance if <code>percentDiffForMaxScale</code> is 10 (10%), a
255    * difference of 5% will have a half shade of red/green, a difference of
256    * 10% or more will have a maximum shade/brightness of red/green.
257    * <P>
258    * The chart object returned by this method uses a {@link PiePlot} instance
259    * as the plot.
260    * <p>
261    * Written by <a href="mailto:opensource@objectlab.co.uk">Benoit
262    * Xhenseval</a>.
263    *
264    * @param title the chart title (<code>null</code> permitted).
265    * @param dataset the dataset for the chart (<code>null</code> permitted).
266    * @param previousDataset the dataset for the last run, this will be used
267    * to compare each key in the dataset
268    * @param percentDiffForMaxScale scale goes from bright red/green to black,
269    * percentDiffForMaxScale indicate the change
270    * required to reach top scale.
271    * @param greenForIncrease an increase since previousDataset will be
272    * displayed in green (decrease red) if true.
273    * @param legend a flag specifying whether or not a legend is required.
274    * @param tooltips configure chart to generate tool tips?
275    * @param urls configure chart to generate URLs?
276    * @param subTitle displays a subtitle with colour scheme if true
277    * @param showDifference create a new dataset that will show the %
278    * difference between the two datasets.
279    *
280    * @return A pie chart.
281    */
